<h1>Managing Your Notes: A Quick Guide</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
    This guide will help you manage your notes effectively using our note management software. 
    Whether you're creating a new note, editing an existing one, or organizing your notes, these 
    step-by-step instructions will make the process simple and seamless.
</p>

<h2>Features and Functions</h2>

<h3>1. Creating a Note</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Access the Notes Section:</strong> Click on the "Notes" tab in the main menu.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Start a New Note:</strong> Click the <strong>"Add Note"</strong> button.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Enter Details:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Add a meaningful title to your note.</li>
            <li><strong>Content:</strong> Use the text editor to write your note.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Save Your Note:</strong> Once done, click the <strong>"Save"</strong> button.
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>2. Viewing Your Notes</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Go to the Notes List:</strong> From the "Notes" tab, view all your saved notes 
        displayed in a list or grid format.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Search Notes:</strong> Use the search bar at the top to find specific notes by title or keywords.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Filter Notes:</strong> Apply filters such as date, tags, or categories to narrow down the list.
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>3. Editing a Note</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Select a Note:</strong> Click on the note you want to edit from the list.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Edit Details:</strong> Update the title or content in the editor.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Save Changes:</strong> Click the <strong>"Update"</strong> button to save your changes.
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>4. Deleting a Note</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Choose a Note:</strong> Locate the note you wish to delete in the list.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Delete Action:</strong> Click on the <strong>"Delete"</strong> icon (trash bin) 
        next to the note or within the note view.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Confirm Deletion:</strong> A confirmation dialog will appear. Click <strong>"Yes"</strong> 
        to permanently delete the note.
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Common Issues and Troubleshooting</h2>

<h3>Q: I can't find a specific note.</h3>
<p>
    <strong>Solution:</strong> Use the search bar or filters to locate the note. Ensure that the note was saved successfully.
</p>

<h3>Q: I accidentally deleted a note. Can I recover it?</h3>
<p>
    <strong>Solution:</strong> Check the <strong>"Trash"</strong> section (if available). Notes are stored there temporarily before permanent deletion.
</p>

<h3>Q: My changes aren’t saving.</h3>
<p>
    <strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure you’re connected to the internet (if the app syncs online) and check that your session hasn’t timed out.
</p>

